0. ROLES
   a. "Lead Owners" refers to  bre4d777 and mooncarli, who jointly hold
      final decision-making authority over the Software, this license,
      and the project's direction. Decisions require agreement between
      the Lead Owners; in the event of a dispute between them, this
      license does not resolve it and they must settle it between
      themselves.
   b. "Contributors" are individuals who submit accepted changes to
      the Software. Contributors are credited as co-owners of the
      project for recognition purposes (Section 1b), but do not hold
      individual control, veto power, or decision-making authority
      over the Software, the org, or this license. All such authority
      rests solely with the Lead Owners.
   c. By submitting a contribution (pull request, patch, or similar),
      a Contributor grants the Lead Owners and the project a perpetual,
      irrevocable, worldwide license to use, modify, relicense, and
      distribute that contribution as part of the Software, while
      retaining their credit as a Contributor.

1. OWNERSHIP
   a. The Software, including all modifications, forks, and derivative
      works, remains the property of the Lead Owners and credited
      Contributors collectively (the "Owners").
   b. Contributors are recognized as co-owners for credit, attribution,
      and reputational purposes only. Final authority over use,
      licensing, enforcement, and direction of the Software belongs
      exclusively to the Lead Owners.
   c. Forking or modifying the Software does not transfer or grant
      ownership to the person doing so, and does not make them an
      Owner or Contributor unless their changes are formally accepted
      into the official repository.

2. PERMITTED USE
   You are permitted, free of charge, to:
     a. View and study the source code.
     b. Use the Software for personal, non-commercial purposes.
     c. Modify the Software for personal use or to contribute back
        to the original repository.
     d. Fork the repository, provided the fork remains public,
        retains this license unmodified, and clearly credits the
        original Owners and repository in the README and source
        headers.

3. REQUIRED CREDIT
   Any use, copy, fork, or modification of the Software — public or
   private — must retain:
     a. This license file, unmodified.
     b. Clear and visible credit to "mooncarli, bre4d777, and OpenUwu
        Contributors" with a link to the original repository, in
        the README and in any user-facing interface (e.g. bot
        "about"/"info" command, application footer, etc.) where
        such credit can reasonably be displayed.

4. PROHIBITED USES
   You may NOT, under any circumstances:
     a. Sell, rent, sublicense, or otherwise charge money for the
        Software or any derivative/modified version of it.
     b. Offer the Software or a modified version as a paid product,
        paid service, or behind a paywall (including donations
        framed as required payment for access).
     c. Remove, obscure, or alter credit/attribution to the Owners.
     d. Re-upload, redistribute, or present the Software (or a
        modified version) as your own original work ("code
        stealing"), including publishing it under a different
        license or claiming authorship.
     e. Use the Software, or any derivative of it, in a closed-source
        or private commercial product.

5. MODIFICATIONS REMAIN OPEN
   Any modified or derivative version of the Software must:
     a. Be made publicly available under this exact same license.
     b. Remain free to access and use under the same terms.
     c. Continue to credit the original Owners, in addition to
